&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-assignment/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-assignment/> ;
  schema:name "Assignment" ;
  schema:description "An Assignment is a triple (Q, C, B) — an assignor Q who holds a Hohfeldian claim C in H*_{t*}, an assignee B who receives C, and an assignment act α that moves C's section from Q's authority domain to B's authority domain. The defining structure: assignment transfers the right (the Hohfeldian claim — Q's right to receive) without changing the correlative duty (the obligor's duty to perform). The obligor P's duty is unchanged; only the identity of the party to whom P owes performance changes from Q to B. Formally: assignment is a natural transformation α : H_Q → H_B between Q's and B's authority presheaves that carries C's settled section from Q's fiber to B's fiber, leaving the duty-fibration unchanged." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:about &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/terms/assignment/> ;
  rdfs:seeAlso "HohfeldianPosition, Right, Duty, Delegation, Novation, Contract, Waiver, Person" ;
  schema:identifier &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-assignment/> .

